webpackJsonp([0x93f052013fcc],{7725:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{post:{html:'<p>From an article on the <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/08/education/08germany.html">Jacobs University Bremen</a> (via <a href="http://andrewhammel.typepad.com/german_joys/2006/11/private_donatio.html">German Joys</a>), which recently changed its name after receiving a $250 million donations from a certain Herr Jacobs:</p>\n<blockquote><p>\n  German universities lack the resources of their American rivals. The United States spends 2.6 percent of its gross domestic product on higher education; the Germans, only 1.1 percent.\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>I guess because Germany would rather spend money on the past (like coal subsidies) than on the future. The closing quote was also cute.</p>\n<blockquote><p>\n  Why didnt Mr. Jacobs give his millions to his own alma mater, the University of Hamburg? They didnt ask.\n</p></blockquote>',fields:{title:"We Don't Need No Education",date:"08 Nov 2006",url:"https://papascott.de/2006-11-08-we-dont-need-no-education/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2006-11-08-we-dont-need-no-education/",prev:{fields:{title:"Macaca!",date:"08 Nov 2006",slug:"/2006-11-08-macaca/"}},next:{fields:{title:"Not My Pod",date:"11 Nov 2006",slug:"/2006-11-11-not-my-pod/"}}}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---2006-11-08-we-dont-need-no-education-9692d48688b25e9b61b9.js.map